Durban - An Ixopo farm owner has appeared in court for drug dealing after police discovered a hydroponic dagga lab at his Richmond premises this week. Russell Galbright (46) made a brief appearance in the Ixopo Magistrate's Court and was released on R1000 Â bail. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo, Hawks media liasion said Hawks officers conducted a search on Galbright's farm at Byrne Village in Richmond on Wednesday. "Members pounced in one of the farms after information was received about the hydroponic laboratory operating in the area. A search was conducted and members found dagga plants, LSD liquid and hashish (hydroponic) with the street value of approximately R260 000. The equipment used was also seized," Mhlongo said. Galbright appeared in the Ixopo Magistrate's Court on a charge of dealing in dagga. He was granted R1 000 bail and is due back in court on October 19.
Hydroponic dagga is harvested in a lab, without the use of soil. It is said to be one of the more stronger types of dagga Daily News